SUMMARY:Hiller Aviation Museum (San Carlos)
DESCRIPTION:A hangar full of real planes and helicopters where your littl
 e guy can climb into a Boeing 747 cockpit\, watch planes overhead\, and 
 build with giant foam blocks at the Imagination Playground. Indoor and e
 asy.\n\nDrive: ~35 min from Fremont\nWebsite: https://www.hiller.org
LOCATION:Hiller Aviation Museum\, 601 Skyway Rd\, San Carlos CA
URL:https://www.hiller.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:summer2026-toddler-2@weekend-adventures
DTSTAMP:20260621T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260718
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260720
SUMMARY:Ferry Ride Across the Bay (SF Ferry Building to Sausalito)
DESCRIPTION:His first time out on the open water - board the Golden Gate 
 Ferry at the SF Ferry Building and glide 30 minutes across the Bay to Sa
 usalito\, with the Golden Gate Bridge\, Alcatraz\, and the skyline drift
 ing by. Kids under 5 ride free.\n\nDrive: ~45 min to the Ferry Building\
 nWebsite: https://www.goldengate.org/ferry/
LOCATION:San Francisco Ferry Building\, San Francisco CA
URL:https://www.goldengate.org/ferry/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:summer2026-toddler-3@weekend-adventures
DTSTAMP:20260621T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260725
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260727
SUMMARY:Parent-and-Me Swim Class (La Petite Baleen\, Redwood City)
DESCRIPTION:A first splash in the warm-water pool at La Petite Baleen\, a
  beloved Bay Area swim school since 1979. You are in the water with him 
 the whole time\, learning songs\, gentle floats\, and bubble-blowing in 
 a cozy 90-degree pool. Call ahead to book a trial class.\n\nDrive: ~35 m
 in from Fremont\nWebsite: https://www.swimlpb.com/
LOCATION:La Petite Baleen Swim School\, 60 Fifth Ave\, Redwood City CA
URL:https://www.swimlpb.com/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:summer2026-toddler-4@weekend-adventures
DTSTAMP:20260621T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260801
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260803
SUMMARY:Music & Movement Class (Music Together (local class))
DESCRIPTION:His first morning of shakers\, drums\, scarves\, and silly so
 ngs in a circle of families. Music Together's mixed-age classes are pure
  joy for a 19-month-old. Use the finder to pick the closest Tri-City cla
 ss and drop into a free demo.\n\nDrive: ~15 min from Fremont\nWebsite: h
 ttps://www.musictogether.com/find-a-class
LOCATION:Music Together class Fremont CA
URL:https://www.musictogether.com/find-a-class
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:summer2026-toddler-5@weekend-adventures
DTSTAMP:20260621T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260808
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260810
SUMMARY:Niles Canyon Railway Train Ride (Sunol Depot)
DESCRIPTION:A genuine vintage train ride right in your backyard - climb a
 board a historic coach at the Sunol Depot and rumble through scenic Nile
 s Canyon alongside the creek and oak hills. Aug 8 is a scheduled diesel 
 run\; departures 10:30am & 1pm. Kids 2 & under free - buy tickets online
  ahead.\n\nDrive: ~20 min from Fremont\nWebsite: https://www.ncry.org/ri
 de/2026-train-rides/
LOCATION:Niles Canyon Railway\, 6 Kilkare Rd\, Sunol CA
URL:https://www.ncry.org/ride/2026-train-rides/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:summer2026-toddler-6@weekend-adventures
DTSTAMP:20260621T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260815
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260817
SUMMARY:The Little Gym Parent-Child Class (The Little Gym of Milpitas)
DESCRIPTION:A whole gym made for wobbly little movers - soft beams to tod
 dle across\, mats to roll on\, bars to hang from\, and a parachute final
 e. The Beasts parent-child class (19-35 months) is built for busy boys h
 is age. Try a free intro class.\n\nDrive: ~15 min from Fremont\nWebsite:
  https://www.thelittlegym.com/california-milpitas/
LOCATION:The Little Gym of Milpitas CA
URL:https://www.thelittlegym.com/california-milpitas/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:summer2026-toddler-7@weekend-adventures
DTSTAMP:20260621T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260822
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260824
SUMMARY:Coastal Cabin Stay - Costanoa\, Pescadero (Pescadero (San Mateo C
 oast))
DESCRIPTION:A laid-back eco-resort between the coastal hills and the sea.
  Rent a cozy cabin or family cottage with its own fire pit\, roast a fre
 e marshmallow at the nightly Sunset S'mores\, wander easy nature trails 
 spotting deer and bunnies\, and stroll the dune boardwalk to a wild\, qu
 iet beach.\n\nDrive: ~1 hr 20 min from Fremont\nWebsite: https://www.cos
 tanoa.com/
LOCATION:Costanoa Lodge\, 2001 Rossi Rd\, Pescadero CA
URL:https://www.costanoa.com/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:summer2026-toddler-8@weekend-adventures
DTSTAMP:20260621T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260829
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260831
SUMMARY:CuriOdyssey (San Mateo)
DESCRIPTION:A bayside science playground where toddlers push\, pour\, and
  poke at interactive exhibits and meet rescued native animals up close. 
 Small\, manageable\, and endlessly touchable - a great first museum of d
 iscovery.\n\nDrive: ~35 min from Fremont\nWebsite: https://curiodyssey.o
 rg
LOCATION:CuriOdyssey San Mateo CA
URL:https://curiodyssey.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:summer2026-toddler-9@weekend-adventures
DTSTAMP:20260621T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260905
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260907
SUMMARY:Children's Creativity Museum (San Francisco)
DESCRIPTION:Hands-on art and play studios in Yerba Buena Gardens with a d
 edicated toddler area - their first finger-paint\, first building blocks
  - and the beloved 1906 carousel right outside. Labor Day weekend pick.\
 n\nDrive: ~45 min from Fremont\nWebsite: https://creativity.org
LOCATION:Children's Creativity Museum San Francisco CA
URL:https://creativity.org
